  "text": "In our approach, a single trajectory hypothesis is defined as an ordered list of target tracklets, i.e. Γ i = {l i1 , l i2 , ..., l i k } where l i k ∈ L. The association trajectory hypothesis Γ is defined as a set of single trajectory hypothesis, i.e. Γ = {Γ i }. The objective of data association is to maximize the posteriori probability of Γ given the tracklets set L under the non-overlap constraints [CITATION_1] :",
